    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.34537/108.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 169.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 477 of the 23d ultimo, I
                    enclose for your information a copy of a letter<note n="3" xml:id="d419fn3">Not
                        printed.</note> from the Acting Secretary of the Navy expressing his
                    approval of the final text of the proposed convention for the enlargement of the
                    Guantánamo naval station on the understanding that the rent as proposed by the
                    new agreement covers the entire tract as enlarged.</p>
                <p>Your full powers will be sent to you within a few days, and you may conclude the
                    convention at Habana, either engrossing it at the <pb facs="0411" n="295"
                        xml:id="pg_295"/> Legation or requesting the Cuban Foreign Office to engross
                    both copies. You will of course compare the copies, English and Spanish,
                    carefully before signature.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
